WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:58.310
Monsters of the Grand Line

3
00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:17.830
Front Entrance
Arlong Park

4
00:02:21.370 --> 00:02:22.830
Guess that's good enough...

5
00:02:27.340 --> 00:02:31.130
Momoo! Time to eat! Momoo!

6
00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:34.090
That's strange...

7
00:02:34.090 --> 00:02:37.720
He should be starving
right about now.

8
00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:39.060
Where could he have gone?

9
00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:48.270
Mr. Gen!

10
00:02:50.780 --> 00:02:53.400
Possessing weapons
is a clear act of rebellion!

11
00:02:53.400 --> 00:02:56.450
To stop any more rebels
like you from emerging,

12
00:02:56.450 --> 00:03:01.160
I'm going to kill you right now
as an example to the other humans!

13
00:03:01.990 --> 00:03:06.920
No way! He'll kill someone
just for having weapons?!

14
00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:08.290
He has no right!

15
00:03:08.290 --> 00:03:10.130
H-H-Hey, you! Hey! Hey!

16
00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:13.840
You have no right to do this, Arlong!

17
00:03:16.300 --> 00:03:21.430
We've paid you tribute money
for eight years straight!

18
00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:24.270
Why would we suddenly
want to rebel now?!

19
00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:26.520
Put Mr. Gen down!

20
00:03:28.860 --> 00:03:30.060
Yeah!

21
00:03:30.060 --> 00:03:32.780
It's not like he used
any of the weapons!

22
00:03:32.780 --> 00:03:33.820
Stop it!

23
00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:35.650
Let Mr. Gen go!

24
00:03:36.150 --> 00:03:40.120
I'm saying that the possession
of weapons indicates the will to rebel.

25
00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:44.580
Perhaps I ought to wipe
this village off the map.

26
00:03:45.160 --> 00:03:50.750
If just one of you lays a hand on us,
your village will meet its demise.

27
00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:53.300
I don't care either way!

28
00:03:54.050 --> 00:03:55.800
Get inside, everyone!

29
00:03:56.800 --> 00:04:00.390
If we cause trouble now,
the last eight years will be wasted!

30
00:04:00.390 --> 00:04:03.770
If we wanted to defiantly
fight to our deaths,

31
00:04:03.770 --> 00:04:06.770
then the time to do so
would've been eight years ago!

32
00:04:06.770 --> 00:04:14.230
We all swore that enduring it would
be our fight. We swore to live!

33
00:04:15.110 --> 00:04:16.110
Mr. Gen!

34
00:04:16.110 --> 00:04:17.200
But...

35
00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:20.570
Such wise words!
You can really give a speech!

36
00:04:20.570 --> 00:04:23.580
Yes! Being alive is a good thing!

37
00:04:23.580 --> 00:04:26.750
Even for puny insects like you!

38
00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:29.250
Mr. Gen!

39
00:04:30.630 --> 00:04:34.630
Not all living things are born equal!

40
00:04:36.420 --> 00:04:37.300
Damn you...!

41
00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:37.880
Stop!

42
00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:41.340
Don't touch them!

43
00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:42.800
But, Mr. Gen...!

44
00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:48.230
If you die, it's all over!

45
00:04:48.230 --> 00:04:50.770
Don't stop fighting this
battle of endurance!

46
00:04:51.270 --> 00:04:52.810
Even if I die...

47
00:04:52.810 --> 00:04:54.940
Nice resolve!

48
00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:57.320
Pay close attention, humans!

49
00:04:58.070 --> 00:05:02.820
This is what happens to those who
show even a hint of sedition!

50
00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:04.620
Exploding Star!

51
00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:09.410
Wh-What was that?!

52
00:05:10.540 --> 00:05:12.210
Look! Up there!

53
00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:15.590
There's someone on the roof!

54
00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:18.880
Who the hell are you?!

55
00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:24.720
My name is Captain Usopp,
brave warrior of the sea!

56
00:05:26.060 --> 00:05:27.430
It's him...!

57
00:05:27.430 --> 00:05:29.680
Th-The world fears me

58
00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:32.810
and calls me Demon King Usopp,
the man from the netherworld!

59
00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:34.900
I'll give you one
last chance to run away!

60
00:05:34.900 --> 00:05:36.400
I have 8,000–

61
00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:38.440
Captain Arlong! That's him!

62
00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:41.070
The guy who got away earlier!

63
00:05:41.070 --> 00:05:44.370
Bring tens of thousands
of men if you want.

64
00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:47.870
I'll tear apart every last one!

65
00:05:49.410 --> 00:05:52.250
My exploding star didn't
scare him or anything!

66
00:05:52.250 --> 00:05:54.750
How dare a human...

67
00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:58.250
a lowly, worthless human
do this to me?!

68
00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:06.850
Captain Arlong! Wait!

69
00:06:06.850 --> 00:06:10.680
We'll lose another
source of cash, like Gosa!

70
00:06:11.020 --> 00:06:16.900
Human villages are easy to destroy,
but our goal is to rule them!

71
00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:19.360
If we crush some, we'll just find more!

72
00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:23.150
We are the supreme species!

73
00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:25.410
He's wrecking the village!

74
00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:30.290
Is he...?!

75
00:06:31.830 --> 00:06:33.410
I'm gonna die! I'm gonna die!

76
00:06:33.660 --> 00:06:36.460
H-He's still alive! After him!

77
00:06:34.830 --> 00:06:35.630
Crap!

78
00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:40.380
Catch him and kill him!

79
00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:43.130
Hey! Let's get him
back to Arlong Park!

80
00:06:43.130 --> 00:06:45.510
If this goes on, he'll smash the village!

81
00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:46.340
Yeah!

82
00:06:47.350 --> 00:06:49.350
Don't let him get away!

83
00:06:49.350 --> 00:06:51.350
Who does he take us for?!

84
00:06:51.350 --> 00:06:52.980
We'll be back.

85
00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:55.310
You'll live for now.

86
00:07:01.690 --> 00:07:03.030
I'm sorry...

87
00:07:03.030 --> 00:07:05.110
I caused you all trouble...

88
00:07:05.110 --> 00:07:06.860
What are you talking about?

89
00:07:06.860 --> 00:07:08.450
You didn't do anything wrong!

90
00:07:08.450 --> 00:07:09.410
Yeah!

91
00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:12.200
But who was that youngster?

92
00:07:12.950 --> 00:07:14.460
Everyone!

93
00:07:14.460 --> 00:07:16.000
It's good to see you again!

94
00:07:16.710 --> 00:07:18.500
Nami!

95
00:07:17.460 --> 00:07:18.500
It's Nami!

96
00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:19.420
It's her!

97
00:07:27.010 --> 00:07:28.340
What's going on?

98
00:07:28.340 --> 00:07:30.890
You never walk right
through the village...

99
00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:33.430
I heard a loud noise...

100
00:07:33.430 --> 00:07:34.890
Arlong, huh...?

101
00:07:45.570 --> 00:07:48.320
Just seven million berries left to go.

102
00:07:49.410 --> 00:07:52.830
Your reputation is as horrible as ever.

103
00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:55.660
That's fine. I'm a pirate, after all!

104
00:07:55.660 --> 00:07:58.080
Arlong is surprisingly reasonable.

105
00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:00.380
Money will fix all this.

106
00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:03.880
I've almost fulfilled my
agreement with Arlong.

107
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:09.760
Whatever it takes,
I'll earn 100 million berries

108
00:08:09.760 --> 00:08:11.430
and buy this village!

109
00:08:14.890 --> 00:08:19.650
She tells me to run, but this is
exactly the place I'm supposed to be.

110
00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:23.860
I mean, I promised Luffy
I'd bring that girl back.

111
00:08:23.860 --> 00:08:26.740
Well then, what should I do now?

112
00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:28.610
Things are starting to get messy.

113
00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:32.910
I told you, that's mine!

114
00:08:40.920 --> 00:08:43.250
Okay, I'm sorry! You can have this!

115
00:08:43.250 --> 00:08:45.130
You know I can't eat that!

116
00:08:45.130 --> 00:08:47.420
I'm not a dog, dammit!

117
00:08:48.630 --> 00:08:49.630
Quiet!

118
00:08:57.890 --> 00:08:58.890
It's big...

119
00:08:58.890 --> 00:08:59.600
Huh?

120
00:09:05.400 --> 00:09:06.820
What's that?

121
00:09:09.530 --> 00:09:13.620
A sea monster!

122
00:09:09.570 --> 00:09:14.370
Momoo the Sea Cow
Heavy Combat Beast
Arlong Pirates

123
00:09:14.740 --> 00:09:16.990
That cow is huge!

124
00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.250
A cow? They don't swim.

125
00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:21.330
It's gotta be a hippo.

126
00:09:21.330 --> 00:09:24.170
What's something like this
doing in the East Blue?!

127
00:09:24.170 --> 00:09:27.130
It's a creature from the Grand Line!

128
00:09:29.760 --> 00:09:30.840
Huh?

129
00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:32.550
What's this guy doing?

130
00:09:36.220 --> 00:09:37.680
He's after the food!

131
00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:38.430
What?!

132
00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:39.770
Hurry and give it to him!

133
00:09:39.770 --> 00:09:41.140
He'll capsize the boat!

134
00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:43.940
Gum-Gum Pistol!

135
00:09:48.320 --> 00:09:50.570
Stay away from my lunch!

136
00:09:50.570 --> 00:09:52.910
You did it! Incredible, Big Bro Luffy!

137
00:09:56.370 --> 00:09:57.870
Looks like you made it mad!

138
00:09:57.870 --> 00:09:59.250
Want some more?!

139
00:09:59.250 --> 00:10:00.450
You dumbass!

140
00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:03.290
Don't mindlessly beat up
a poor, hungry creature!

141
00:10:04.250 --> 00:10:07.880
He's probably hurt or something
and can't catch his own food.

142
00:10:07.880 --> 00:10:09.630
Isn't that right?

143
00:10:09.630 --> 00:10:11.340
How sweet.

144
00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:13.260
Here, eat up.

145
00:10:13.260 --> 00:10:15.510
No need to be shy.

146
00:10:21.390 --> 00:10:23.520
Die, damn you!

147
00:10:26.230 --> 00:10:30.480
What was that for?!
What happened to that sweetness?!

148
00:10:30.480 --> 00:10:33.280
That bastard was about to
eat me along with the food.

149
00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:39.490
Here he comes! He'll sink the boat!

150
00:10:39.490 --> 00:10:40.330
That jerk!

151
00:10:40.330 --> 00:10:42.000
Get back. I'll do it.

152
00:10:46.420 --> 00:10:49.380
Collier Shoot!

153
00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:53.720
Damn hippo...

154
00:10:58.140 --> 00:11:00.760
Alright! Back to eating!

155
00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:02.600
Not a bad workout.

156
00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:04.850
These guys are crazy...

157
00:11:07.440 --> 00:11:08.940
What's taking so long?!

158
00:11:13.190 --> 00:11:15.780
When is Luffy gonna show up?!

159
00:11:15.780 --> 00:11:18.950
Five more minutes
and I'm gonna die of boredom!

160
00:11:22.240 --> 00:11:23.700
Incredible!

161
00:11:23.700 --> 00:11:28.290
Not even Hatchan, great octopus officer
of the Arlong Pirates, can pull you up!

162
00:11:28.290 --> 00:11:30.790
You're a super-grade fish!

163
00:11:30.790 --> 00:11:36.090
I dunno who you are, but you're
the gutsiest fish in the East Blue!

164
00:11:36.090 --> 00:11:37.800
Whoa! What the...?!

165
00:11:37.800 --> 00:11:39.180
Oh!

166
00:11:39.180 --> 00:11:41.060
It was me all along?

167
00:11:43.310 --> 00:11:47.140
I really am the gutsiest
in the East Blue.

168
00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:49.650
Wait, does that seem strange?

169
00:11:50.270 --> 00:11:51.320
Sure does.

170
00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:54.900
Wh-Who are you?!

171
00:11:56.570 --> 00:11:57.490
Me?

172
00:11:57.490 --> 00:11:59.530
I'm Hatchan!

173
00:11:59.530 --> 00:12:01.410
Call me Hachi!

174
00:12:01.410 --> 00:12:03.290
Are you a fishman, too?

175
00:12:03.290 --> 00:12:07.540
Of course, of course!
I'm a ravishing octopus fishman!

176
00:12:07.540 --> 00:12:09.710
From the looks of it, you're a human?

177
00:12:09.710 --> 00:12:10.580
Y-Yeah.

178
00:12:10.580 --> 00:12:13.340
A marine? Or maybe a guest?

179
00:12:13.670 --> 00:12:14.880
Guest?

180
00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:18.010
I guess you could say I'm a guest.

181
00:12:18.010 --> 00:12:20.220
Captain Arlong isn't here
right now, is he?

182
00:12:20.220 --> 00:12:21.930
Nope. Where'd he go?

183
00:12:21.930 --> 00:12:27.350
Apparently, there's a long-nosed
outsider running all over the place.

184
00:12:27.350 --> 00:12:29.980
Arlong went to catch him
in Cocoyashi Village

185
00:12:29.980 --> 00:12:33.070
after he locked up his buddy here.

186
00:12:33.480 --> 00:12:35.190
Usopp, huh...?

187
00:12:35.190 --> 00:12:36.990
Guess I'll go save him.

188
00:12:39.240 --> 00:12:41.120
This Cocoyashi Village...

189
00:12:42.160 --> 00:12:42.990
How do I get there?

190
00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:44.120
Get in.

191
00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:48.290
You're a guest, aren't you?

192
00:12:48.290 --> 00:12:49.580
I'll take you there,

193
00:12:50.210 --> 00:12:51.830
swordsman.

194
00:13:04.260 --> 00:13:06.930
Damn! I can't lose 'em!

195
00:13:10.730 --> 00:13:12.520
Wh-Where is he?

196
00:13:13.230 --> 00:13:17.570
Who here thinks the Unbelievable Usopp's
death would be a great waste of talent?

197
00:13:17.570 --> 00:13:18.690
Me!

198
00:13:18.690 --> 00:13:20.700
Me! Me! Me! Me!

199
00:13:21.070 --> 00:13:23.490
What's this idiot up to?!

200
00:13:23.870 --> 00:13:25.950
Oh, you guys think so, too?

201
00:13:25.950 --> 00:13:27.120
I agree!

202
00:13:33.040 --> 00:13:34.040
Wh-What?

203
00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:38.710
Lethal Egg Star!

204
00:13:48.470 --> 00:13:51.230
How'd ya like that?! I guess
fishmen aren't so superior!

205
00:13:51.230 --> 00:13:53.900
Looks like every one of 'em
let Captain Usopp escape!

206
00:13:56.320 --> 00:13:57.650
I-I don't know!

207
00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:10.660
Huh?

208
00:14:10.660 --> 00:14:11.410
What?

209
00:14:14.670 --> 00:14:16.630
Thanks for your cheers!

210
00:14:16.630 --> 00:14:19.840
As you can see, I'm very much alive!

211
00:14:24.720 --> 00:14:26.430
Here's Cocoyashi Village.

212
00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:29.010
Captain Arlong should be here.

213
00:14:29.010 --> 00:14:30.520
Huh? Oh, great. Thanks.

214
00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:33.100
No problem! Bye, now!

215
00:14:35.730 --> 00:14:39.270
Whoops! I just remembered,
I forgot to ask your name!

216
00:14:39.270 --> 00:14:42.780
Huh? Me? Why are you
asking for my name again?

217
00:14:42.780 --> 00:14:44.320
It's Hatchan!

218
00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:46.160
Come back again!

219
00:14:47.570 --> 00:14:48.780
What a strange guy.

220
00:15:01.630 --> 00:15:03.920
Wh-What the hell happened?!

221
00:15:05.930 --> 00:15:07.680
What happened here...

222
00:15:10.260 --> 00:15:12.720
my brothers?!

223
00:15:14.850 --> 00:15:16.310
Roronoa...

224
00:15:17.940 --> 00:15:20.360
What? What are you trying to say?!

225
00:15:21.110 --> 00:15:23.570
Roronoa Zoro...!

226
00:15:23.570 --> 00:15:24.570
What?!

227
00:15:24.570 --> 00:15:26.530
The Pirate Hunter?!

228
00:15:26.530 --> 00:15:28.820
Did he come for my bounty?!

229
00:15:31.330 --> 00:15:34.790
N-No, he didn't come... Th-That guy...

230
00:15:35.580 --> 00:15:36.920
He was... Zoro!

231
00:15:36.920 --> 00:15:37.960
What?!

232
00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:42.840
That bellyband guy
we caught was Roronoa...

233
00:15:47.760 --> 00:15:49.140
I caught him!

234
00:15:50.100 --> 00:15:52.180
Wh-What in the world?!

235
00:15:53.180 --> 00:15:55.100
W-Was all this Zoro...?!

236
00:15:58.520 --> 00:16:03.650
Catching this scum isn't nearly
enough to satisfy my hunger!

237
00:16:05.070 --> 00:16:08.320
Y-Yeah, right?!
So you should let me go!

238
00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:10.030
I was just saying hello earlier!

239
00:16:10.030 --> 00:16:12.830
Th-That's how we do it in my village!

240
00:16:15.540 --> 00:16:18.870
But you're one of Zoro's men.

241
00:16:20.330 --> 00:16:24.960
Well, it's only natural for famous
bounty hunters to come after me.

242
00:16:27.670 --> 00:16:29.760
Don't kill me!

243
00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:34.100
I don't have anything to do
with that Zoro guy!

244
00:16:34.970 --> 00:16:36.930
Enough of your blatant lies.

245
00:16:36.930 --> 00:16:39.140
You also stood against
Captain Arlong.

246
00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:41.560
Looks like you're
going to die either way.

247
00:16:42.940 --> 00:16:47.570
H-Hey! As a matter of fact,
Zoro and I are really close!

248
00:16:47.570 --> 00:16:49.570
So just try and lay a finger on me!

249
00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:51.370
Zoro won't stand by quietly!

250
00:16:51.370 --> 00:16:52.240
Oh?

251
00:16:52.240 --> 00:16:56.200
Which means if I kill you,
Zoro will come back?

252
00:16:57.960 --> 00:17:00.080
N-No, wait, that's not right!

253
00:17:00.080 --> 00:17:04.090
Killing me is a bad idea! If you
keep me alive, Zoro will show up!

254
00:17:04.090 --> 00:17:07.380
Actually, Zoro will only
show up if you keep me alive!

255
00:17:07.880 --> 00:17:10.050
But how exactly did Zoro...

256
00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:12.760
escape from our prison?

257
00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:14.260
What do you mean?

258
00:17:14.260 --> 00:17:16.890
What I mean is,
someone let him escape.

259
00:17:18.180 --> 00:17:19.810
Captain Arlong.

260
00:17:19.810 --> 00:17:22.060
Does this sound plausible to you?

261
00:17:22.060 --> 00:17:27.230
Perhaps Nami let Zoro infiltrate
our turf so he could take your head?

262
00:17:27.900 --> 00:17:31.200
N-Now that you mention it,
Nami was acting strange earlier.

263
00:17:31.200 --> 00:17:34.240
Yeah. She even saved Zoro
when he jumped into the water.

264
00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:37.370
Don't tell me she was working
with Zoro from the very start...

265
00:17:37.370 --> 00:17:38.870
She tricked us all?!

266
00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:43.170
Betrayal is her specialty.

267
00:17:43.670 --> 00:17:45.340
That's enough!

268
00:17:47.750 --> 00:17:50.920
Conjecture won't get you anywhere!

269
00:17:52.260 --> 00:17:53.090
Nami...

270
00:17:53.720 --> 00:17:55.600
Watch what you say!

271
00:17:56.100 --> 00:17:59.350
Eight years ago, I got this tattoo...

272
00:18:00.600 --> 00:18:02.940
as my oath of loyalty to this crew!

273
00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:06.610
Sorry, sorry.

274
00:18:06.610 --> 00:18:07.440
Nami.

275
00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:10.280
Obviously, we've upset you.

276
00:18:10.280 --> 00:18:15.870
But relax. I don't suspect you at all.

277
00:18:15.870 --> 00:18:18.950
We've known each other
for eight years now!

278
00:18:19.410 --> 00:18:22.410
We were just a little on edge.

279
00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:24.830
Right, Nami?

280
00:18:24.830 --> 00:18:29.210
The ones we need to get rid of
are Roronoa Zoro and his group!

281
00:18:29.210 --> 00:18:30.800
H-Hey, Nami!

282
00:18:30.800 --> 00:18:33.300
S-Say something!

283
00:18:33.300 --> 00:18:34.840
N-Nami!

284
00:18:37.550 --> 00:18:39.970
Zoro just had to make trouble...

285
00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.270
What's wrong, Nami?

286
00:18:47.110 --> 00:18:49.440
You look a little pale.

287
00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:53.110
As for long-nose here...

288
00:18:54.280 --> 00:18:57.870
not even you can save him now.

289
00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:01.040
Not after he's defied Captain Arlong.

290
00:19:01.040 --> 00:19:02.160
How long...

291
00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:05.290
How long are you going
to suspect me?!

292
00:19:05.290 --> 00:19:08.090
You're too clever, you see.

293
00:19:08.090 --> 00:19:11.800
I almost have the money
Arlong and I agreed to!

294
00:19:11.800 --> 00:19:13.590
Why would I betray you now?!

295
00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:15.220
I'm well aware...

296
00:19:15.970 --> 00:19:21.390
that eight years ago you agreed to pay
Arlong 100 million berries for Cocoyashi village.

297
00:19:22.890 --> 00:19:25.520
I just can't make sense of it though.

298
00:19:25.890 --> 00:19:31.070
You betrayed both your mother and
the villagers. You only trust money.

299
00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:33.530
Why do you care so much
for Cocoyashi?

300
00:19:33.530 --> 00:19:36.860
Why such a puny little village?

301
00:19:37.360 --> 00:19:40.490
Actually, I found this...

302
00:19:40.830 --> 00:19:42.620
in your room.

303
00:19:46.040 --> 00:19:47.290
Th-That's...

304
00:19:48.130 --> 00:19:49.330
my...

305
00:19:50.420 --> 00:19:52.090
S-Say what?!

306
00:19:52.550 --> 00:19:54.090
Usopp's been captured?!

307
00:19:54.090 --> 00:19:57.590
Yeah! They took him
to Arlong Park a little while ago!

308
00:19:57.590 --> 00:20:00.850
That youngster was brave,
but he defied Arlong!

309
00:20:00.850 --> 00:20:02.600
He's surely dead by now!

310
00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:06.060
Damn...

311
00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:10.560
Why did he have to get caught
right after I killed all that time there?

312
00:20:12.690 --> 00:20:14.940
Usopp! Don't die on me!

313
00:20:29.580 --> 00:20:33.630
Go! To Arlong Park!

314
00:20:46.480 --> 00:20:49.270
Hang on, Nami!
